<TITLE> CSE indices fall on threat news </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 29 (bdnews24.com)The indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange slumped on the news of the bomb threat on Monday on the Dhaka Stock Exchange, an official . Security has been scaled up at the port city bourse, said the official who spoke on condition of anonymity , asking not to be named. The selective categories index or CSCX started the day with a steep rise, pushing the index 57 points up during the first two hours of trading. It fell sharply afterwards to close 29.33 points or 0.44 percent lower to 6609.42. The blue chip, CSE-30 ended on 8153.29, falling 37.76 points or 0.46 percent. Market operators said that the fall might have been influenced by the bomb threat. "The market witnessed a slump which might have been caused by the news of Dhaka Stock Exchange," CSE chief executive Abu Bakar Siddique told bdnews24.com. An apparently hoax bomb threat forced the Dhaka Stock Exchange to shut down an hour earlier than the scheduled close of trading on Monday, an official said. Authorities halted transactions at 1:15pm and then evacuated the building. Different law-enforcing agencies including a joint bomb squad of RAB and the Detective Branch of police were searching the building, police said.
